<div class='communityQuestionSubTitle'>
Popular Answered Questions
</div>
<div id='communityQuestionsWithAnswers'>
<div class='communityQuestionAndAnswer'>
<div class='communityQuestion'>
<div class='questionText'>
<a href="/questions/1335001-how-is-this-a-science-fiction">How is this a science fiction?</a>
</div>
<div class='communityQAFooter questionFooter'>
<ul class='questionFooterActions'>
<li class='footerItem like'>
<span class='likeItContainer' id='like_container_community_question_1335001'><a id="like_count_community_question_1335001" rel="nofollow" href="/rating/voters/1335001?resource_type=CommunityQuestion"><span class="likesCount">3 likes</span></a>&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;<a rel="nofollow" class="jsLike like_it" href="https://www.goodreads.com/user/new?remember=true&amp;return_url=%2Fbook%2Fshow%2F36159.Black_Sun_Rising">like</a></span>

</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionTimestamp'>
<a href="/questions/1335001-how-is-this-a-science-fiction">3 years ago</a>
</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionPermalink'>
<a href="/questions/1335001-how-is-this-a-science-fiction">See all 2 answers</a>
</li>
</ul>
</div>

</div>
<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/24012204-arnstein-pettersen"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1537443934i/24012204._UX100_CR0,10,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/24012204-arnstein-pettersen">Arnstein Pettersen</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">The trilogy feels and behaves mostly like a fantasy story, but the fictional technology is also important. The humans originally came from Earth in a <a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">The trilogy feels and behaves mostly like a fantasy story, but the fictional technology is also important. The humans originally came from Earth in a spaceship and brought a lot of advanced tech with them. This is the fictional science element. Then they land on Erna, a planet with a mystical/magical force (the fantasy element) which the technology reacts poorly to. Much of the story concerns itself with this crash between the two elements, (more so early on than later), and therefore any description of it needs to acknowledge both. I find that 'high fantasy with some sci-fi in it' is a reasonably accurate categorization.<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerFooter'>

<div class='flagAnswer'>
<a class="right flag" rel="nofollow" id="flag_link1184168" title="Flag this answer as inappropriate." href="/flagged/new?resource_id=1184168&amp;resource_type=CommunityAnswer&amp;return_url=%2Fquestions%2F1335001-how-is-this-a-science-fiction%2Fanswers%2F1184168-the-trilogy-feels-and">flag</a>
</div>
<ul class='communityQAFooter answerFooter'>
</ul>

</div>
</div>

</div>

</div>
<div class='communityQuestionAndAnswer'>
<div class='communityQuestion'>
<div class='questionText'>
<a href="/questions/1181289-what-is-the-core-that-the-characters-keep">What is The Core that the characters keep mentioning? A celestial object of some kind. Do they mean the galactic core? They can see it from the planet&#39;s surface? Thought they were talking about a second sun, at first. Now I&#39;m confused.</a>
</div>
<div class='communityQAFooter questionFooter'>
<ul class='questionFooterActions'>
<li class='footerItem like'>
<span class='likeItContainer' id='like_container_community_question_1181289'><a id="like_count_community_question_1181289" rel="nofollow" href="/rating/voters/1181289?resource_type=CommunityQuestion"><span class="likesCount">1 like</span></a>&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;<a rel="nofollow" class="jsLike like_it" href="https://www.goodreads.com/user/new?remember=true&amp;return_url=%2Fbook%2Fshow%2F36159.Black_Sun_Rising">like</a></span>

</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionTimestamp'>
<a href="/questions/1181289-what-is-the-core-that-the-characters-keep">3 years ago</a>
</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionPermalink'>
<a href="/questions/1181289-what-is-the-core-that-the-characters-keep">Add your answer</a>
</li>
</ul>
</div>

</div>
<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/72198494-david-stevens"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1507178662i/72198494._UX100_CR0,0,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/72198494-david-stevens">David Stevens</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
The Core is the center of the galaxy, as I understand it. Erna is so far out on the edge of the galaxy it shows as a giant, bright cluster of stars.
</span>
</div>
</div>
