        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer8464816" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer8251085699637945544">I&apos;m not really sure what I didn&apos;t like about this book. The setting was amazing, the plot was interesting, the characters were... well, they weren&apos;t horrible, but I&apos;ve read better. And that, I think, is where it lost me. I liked the characters well enough, but their problems didn&apos;t engage me. I wasn&apos;t particularly upset when one of the characters died, I wasn&apos;t particularly glad when they resolved some of their issues, and I wasn&apos;t particularly interested to find out what happened to them in the</span>
  <span id="freeText8251085699637945544" style="display:none">I'm not really sure what I didn't like about this book. The setting was amazing, the plot was interesting, the characters were... well, they weren't horrible, but I've read better. And that, I think, is where it lost me. I liked the characters well enough, but their problems didn't engage me. I wasn't particularly upset when one of the characters died, I wasn't particularly glad when they resolved some of their issues, and I wasn't particularly interested to find out what happened to them in the later novels.<br /><br />That's not to say that they aren't <i>good</i>; my roommate is reading the series at the moment, and he loves it. It seems it's just a matter of taste, so I'd say give it a try. They're very interesting and incredibly detailed, just not really my thing.</span>
  <a data-text-id="8251085699637945544" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
