<span id="freeTextContainer12056118452305074280">Yet another book I couldn&apos;t finish. I gave this one a good try - read up to 176 and then asked myself &quot;why am I forcing myself to read a book that bores me?&quot;. The characters are wooden and uninteresting - you learn pretty much nothing about them or even what they look like. The main guy falls in love with the girl in a week and decides to travel to the ends of the planet and face death just to help her. The magic system was not interesting to me and I really dislike the authors writing style. It</span>
  <span id="freeText12056118452305074280" style="display:none">Yet another book I couldn't finish. I gave this one a good try - read up to 176 and then asked myself "why am I forcing myself to read a book that bores me?". The characters are wooden and uninteresting - you learn pretty much nothing about them or even what they look like. The main guy falls in love with the girl in a week and decides to travel to the ends of the planet and face death just to help her. The magic system was not interesting to me and I really dislike the authors writing style. It's hard to know whose POV you're in, it's hard to know who is speaking, and there's pages of description that can easily be skipped over. </span>
  <a data-text-id="12056118452305074280" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

